The paper deals with the combination of radar and optical satellite imagery for land cover classification, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of a neural network architecture, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for processing time series data, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of satellite imagery, which is a common topic in graphics (cs.GR).
